{{Infobox officeholder |name= Magdalena Matte |image= Magdalena Matte.jpg |caption= |alt= |order= |office= [[Ministry of Housing and Urban Development (Chile)|Ministry of Housing and Urban Development]] of [[Chile]] |term_start= 11 March 2010 |term_end= 19 April 2011 |successor= [[Rodrigo Pérez Mackenna]] |predecessor= [[Patricia Poblete|Patricia Poblete Bennett]] |party= [[Independent Democrat Union]] (UDI) |spouse= [[Hernán Larraín Fernández]] |birth_date= |birth_place= [[Santiago]], [[Chile]] |nationality= Chilean |alma_mater= [[Pontifical Catholic University of Chile]] |occupation= [[Civil engineering|Civil Engineer]], [[Businessperson|Businesswoman]], [[Politician]] |religion= [[Catholic Church|Roman Catholicism]] |website= [http://pinera2010.cl/ministerio/vivienda-y-urbanismo/ Pinera2010.cl] }}
'''Magdalena Matte Lecaros''' (born August 13, 1950) is a Chilean [[civil engineering|civil engineer]], [[Businessperson|businesswoman]] and [[politician]]. She is member of the [[Independent Democratic Union]] (UDI) and was part of Chile's [[Ministry of Housing and Urban Development (Chile)|Ministry of Housing and Urban Development]] under Chile's current [[President of Chile|President]] [[Sebastián Piñera]] for the term of 2010-2014. She is a member of the [[Matte family]].
==Biography== Matte was born in [[Santiago]]. Her [[paternal]] grandmother, Rosa Ester Alessandri Rodríguez, was the daughter of [[Arturo Alessandri]], Chile’s president during 1920-1925 and 1932-1938. She is also the sister of [[Jorge Alessandri]], President of Chile between 1958 and 1964. Her paternal grandfather, [[Arturo Matte Larraín]], was a lawyer and congressman, Minister of the State, presidential candidate (1952), and a founder of forestal and paper company [[CMPC (company)|CMPC]].''<ref>{{Es}} La Tercera [http://diario.latercera.com/2010/02/10/01/contenido/13_23586_9.html Perfil empresarial y linaje político marcan a titular de Vivienda]</ref>''
Matte lost her father, [[Arturo Matte Alessandri]], in 1965 when she was 14 years of age. She completed her schooling in Santiago's ''Colegio Santa Úrsula''. She completed her university studies in the [[Pontifical Catholic University of Chile]] majoring in [[civil engineering]]. In 1974, she married [[Hernán Larraín Fernández]], who is a Chilean Senator and former President of the Senate between 2004–2005, with whom she has six children.''<ref>{{Es}} Radio Cooperativa [http://www.cooperativa.cl/prontus_nots/site/artic/20100209/pags/20100209160448.html Magdalena Matte]</ref>''
==Career== She has worked in the private sector, mainly in the company ''Papeleria Dimar'', of which she has been both executive and investor. In 2002, she worked with ''Fondo Confianza'' though the foundation ''La Vaca'', wherein she aided in funding [[entrepreneur]]ial women of low-economic resources. She created 230 work and education centers which cater to 3,000 women in the area of [[Maule Region|El Maule Sur]].
==Politics== On February 9, 2010, Chile’s then-President-elect Sebastián Piñera nominated Magdalena Matte as his Minister of Housing and Urban Development. In April 19 (2011), Magdalena stepped down as minister due to the suspect millionaire compensation payment to the construction company Kodama.<ref>[[La Tercera|La Tercera (Santiago)]], April 17, 2011, Reports, pp.4-6</ref><ref>[http://www.emol.com/noticias/nacional/detalle/detallenoticias.asp?idnoticia=476900 emol, 19 de abril de 2011, 11.03 horas]</ref><ref>[http://www.cooperativa.cl/magdalena-matte-la-quinta-baja-en-el-gabinete-del-presidente-pinera/prontus_nots/2011-04-19/114310.html Radio Cooperativa, April 19, 2011, 11.45 hrs.]</ref><ref>Kodama's case.</ref>
